en_815725_0	A Reverse Osmosis (RO) plant for purification of drinking water for troops in the 65 Division Headquarters in Thunukkai was inaugurated on Tuesday (29).
en_815725_1	Installation of the RO plant fulfilled a long-felt need at the 65 Division since it would have a great impact to prevent Chronic Kidney Diseases (CKD) for troops serving in this area.
en_815725_2	The RO plant has a capacity to provide 5000 liters per day and the General Officer Commanding 65 Division, Major General Wasantha Kumarapperuma commissioned the plant during a brief ceremony.
en_815725_3	Further, arrangements have been made to provide drinking water facility to nearby 653 Brigade and 10 Sri Lanka Light Infantry troops from the same RO plant.
